From: Sergi Perich <info@soploslinux.com>
Date: 2026-07-16
Subject: [PATCH] sched/x86: AMD X3D VCache scheduler preference for Ryzen X3D

Detect asymmetric L3 cache topology in dual-CCD AMD Ryzen X3D processors
(7950X3D, 9950X3D) and bias task wake-up towards the VCache CCD.

On dual-CCD X3D processors one CCD carries 3D VCache stacking, giving it
roughly 3x more L3 than the other CCD (96MB vs 32MB on the 9950X3D).
Gaming and latency-sensitive workloads benefit from running on the VCache
CCD because the larger effective cache reduces cache misses significantly.

Detection happens via a late_initcall after all CPUs are online:
  - Read per-CPU L3 size from the cacheinfo subsystem.
  - If max_l3 > 2 * min_l3 the topology is asymmetric.
  - Mark the larger-L3 CPUs in amd_x3d_vcache_mask.
  - Enable the static key so the scheduler fast-path has zero cost when
    the feature is inactive (symmetric or non-X3D systems).

Scheduling: in select_task_rq_fair(), just before returning new_cpu,
redirect to an idle VCache CPU if one is available within the task's
allowed cpumask and the currently selected CPU is not already on the
VCache CCD.

Only activates on AMD family 0x19+ (Zen 3 and later).
Single-CCD X3D processors (5800X3D, 7800X3D, 9800X3D) are symmetric —
all CPUs report the same L3 size, so the feature stays disabled.

Soplos Linux patch — not for upstream submission.
Applies to Linux 7.x.

Signed-off-by: Sergi Perich <info@soploslinux.com>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/topology.h      |  9 +++
 arch/x86/kernel/cpu/Makefile         |  2 +-
 arch/x86/kernel/cpu/amd_x3d_sched.c | 90 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 kernel/sched/fair.c                  | 32 ++++++++++
 4 files changed, 133 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 arch/x86/kernel/cpu/amd_x3d_sched.c

